I mezz stuff. Then it wakes up and rapes me.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ufurtivus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Furtivus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Newbie Poster</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(12/19/00 8:41:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Raid Board</span><hr size=1> If you haven't already, I suggest checking out www.everquestraids.com  It's a nice board that is a good place to announce your intentions for a raid and/or plan a raid and have people join.  You can guild lock an event if you don't want any non-guild/random invitees along.<br>
<br>
Seems to work pretty well and is a great tool for small guilds looking to have others join them in hunts.  It's also nice (if the board is used) to know who will be where so you can plan a hunt in another location if someone has already planned a raid (or contact that person to find out their raid scheduling/members etc.)<br>
<br>
It's not a scheduling system, but more of a way to announce your intentions.<br>
<br>
Furtivus<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/upalimaxsceleris.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Palimax Sceleris</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Newbie Poster</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(12/19/00 8:44:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3.topic&index=21>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.eqmaps.com/itemicons/2hblunt004.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Re:</span><hr size=1> My $.02 on the subject...<br>
<br>
Vision had intended to move to the following plan to schedule it's planar visits.<br>
<br>
Visit the planes on 2-3 day maximum half-day trips only, GIVING advance notice.<br>
<br>
Example:  Vision will be visiting the Plane of Foo on January 12th-13th starting at 6pm.  Please plan accordingly.  If you are in the zone and wish to coordinate movements, please contact Tolnik.<br>
<br>
Unless someone proposes a plan that (a) doesn't lend itself to favoritism (a council is neat and all, but it'll never meet with universal approval), and (b) doesn't leave people waiting 6 months to visit the planes, this will probably be our plan of action. <p><img src=http://www.goodnet.com/~matts/sig.bmp > </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/usanterre.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Santerre</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Newbie Poster</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(12/19/00 8:51:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Re:</span><hr size=1> Many many people from Solusek Ro still need planar gear.  Guilds that didn't know about the board were asked by GMs to leave the planes on occasion.  Some guilds would go after Gods, not want anyone else in the plane, and let all regular gear rot rather than help anyone else - even if another guild was scheduled and currently in the plane.  Our guild has people that are 58+ still without planar BPs.  I am personally 55th without a planar BP.  Why?  Because in the ONE WEEK we were able to schedule in Fear over the past YEAR, it didn't drop... Unless it did on one of the two days that an uberguild came in and cleared the entire plane before I got home from work.<br>
<br>
I won't be a party to this happening again.  Planes can be one of the most fun experiences in the game.  Don't F it up with some bogus schedule. <p><BR><br><B><I>-Santerre.</I></B></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/uafierra.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Afierra</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Newbie Poster</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(12/19/00 9:07:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> no schedule</span><hr size=1> I for one (as well as my guild) left Karana because of the &quot;famed&quot; KGC.  Sure it had its perks letting the lesser guilds have a chance at the targets, but realistically people should do what they want, when they can.  If Inny is up, take him - if Trak is up, take him.  Simple as that.  If you have the power to gather forces and make your way to some desired target - do it. <p>Afierra Lonecaster
Ragin' Mage 
Nightmare Clan</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ukleg.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kleg</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Newbie Poster</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(12/19/00 10:47:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3.topic&index=24>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Random thoughts</span><hr size=1> Verant really made this issue worse by putting epic weapon item drops in the planes.  Now, we see guilds with members in full Kunark armor clearing a plane just to get to a boss mob.  On CT, alliances of smaller guilds rarely had a chance to kill a god, because the spawn time is static.  Let's acknowledge the fact that some guilds monitor the spawns closely and put themselves in a position to kill a mob shortly after it spawns.  Not a problem unless it means stepping on the toes of another group.  We also have to acknowledge that some people simply don't care if they infringe on another's raid.<br>
<br>
Maybe this will be different on a new server, but I doubt it.  What I'd like to see is better communication between guilds, and perhaps this is the place to do just that.  If a guild needs to get an epic item and plans to raid a plane, they could find out who will be in the zone and work out an arrangement.  Chances are, something can be worked out.  Usually, a bad siutation is caused by a handful of people who aren't reasonable.<br>
<br>
It's possible I'm being too optimistic, but that's just me. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><br><font color=#ff0000>- </font><a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/bayonaero>AyonaeRo</a><font color=#ff0000> - </font><a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm8>Raid Forum</a> <font color=#ff0000> - </font><br><br><br><br>Powered By <a href=http://www.ezboard.com/>ezboard®</a> Ver. 6.9.5.4<br>Copyright ©1999-2002 ezboard, Inc.</center></body></html>  

